FBIS3-52154 "drnes001_r_94001" FBIS-NES-94-001 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Jan 1994 India Belgian Release of JKLF Leader Questioned BK3012130493 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 GMT 30 Dec 93 BK3012130493 Delhi All India Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] In the Rajya Sabha, the opposition today expressed concern over the reported decision of the Belgian Government to deport the JKLF [Jammu Kashmir Liberation Front] chief, Amanullah Khan, to Pakistan. Raising the issue during zero hour [time when there is nothing on the agenda], Mr. J.P. Mathur, BJP [Bharatiya Janata Party]; Mr. I.J. Gujral, Janata Dal; and others said Amanullah Khan was arrested in Brussels on a warrant issued by India. They asked the government to clarify whether the Indian case was effectively presented in the Brussels court.
